Terrorists have attack on the community of the Secretary to the Government of Niger State, Ibrahim Ahmed Matane, burning down 20 houses and cars, and rustling cattle. Our correspondent gathered that Matane in Mashegu Local Government Area was attacked on Tuesday after the terrorists attacked Saho Rami market on Monday. The SSG who confirmed the attack described it as unfortunate and saddening, adding that the government will continue to mount the necessary security structure to address all insecurity challenges in the state. Also confirming the attack on phone, the Commissioner of Local Government, Chieftaincy Affairs and Internal Security, Emmanuel Umar, said the number of casualties could not be ascertained at the time of filing this report. He stated that the bandits are carrying out coordinated attacks from village to village out of frustration as their only escape route to Zamfara state have been blocked by troops. The commissioner further stated that the boarders of the state has been surrounded by troops who have engaged the bandits leading to the bandits recording a large number of casualties in the process. Copyright PUNCH. All rights reserved. This material, and other digital content on this website, may not be reproduced, published, broadcast, rewritten or redistributed in whole or in part without prior express written permission from PUNCH. Contact: theeditor@punchng.com